The paper presents a new algorithm for data deconvolution that involves fitting a superposition of point sources to the measured data. This method has applications in various fields such as imaging, spectroscopy, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) which deals with the processing, transmission, and storage of information. The paper also presents results for fluorescent microscopy images and optical spectra, indicating that it has applications in computer vision (cs.CV), optics and photonics (cs.OE), multimedia (cs.MM), and signal processing (cs.SI).
